===================================================================================
By NARRIC

>Stars and Gods
[tribal, lizard/wolf, hybrid][space, sci-fi, lore, scientific/technological jargon, m/f:POV, mystery, alien planet]~
https://pastebin.com/Sw4N3YNQ
#A terrible accident occurs, leaving Dr Jack Riviera stranded in an unknown yet inhabited world.

===================================================================================
FEEDBACK [WARNING: I am NOT a writer]

> A lot of your lines are very long, cutting them up to shorter lines may help you more easily transfer them from different platforms and make line number referencing more effective
> (line 11) "shows numerous punctures" are we supposed to infer that all the other crew are dead?
> (Line 35, 2nd sentence & Line 67 last sentence) is this meant to be mysterious and vague?
> Tsali and here people were described as living in mud-huts, so I assume that they themselves are quite primitive, but she seems to have a concept of what metal is and the possibility of huge architectural structures, even comparing it to "Corsair plate armour". As a reader I inferred that they either have made contact with metal working civilizations on the planet, or there is more than meets the eye with these natives (mysterious).
> I know some authors like to wait till the human first sees the anthro to better describe in more detail what she actually looks like, even if they have already been introduced, but I feel it is important, specifically for hybrids of this nature, to go into detail when they are first introduced to the reader, so they have a sense of what part is lizard and what part is wolf.

- Azuhmier (aka taganon)
